<p>The <code>tidy</code> tag formats and beautifies HTML content.</p>

<h2>About Tidy</h2>
<p>The tidy tag uses PHP's tidy extension to clean up HTML output.</p>

<h2>Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}tidy{close}
  &lt;html&gt;content&lt;/html&gt;
{open}/tidy{close}</pre>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>The tidy tag requires the PHP tidy extension and appropriate configuration. It's useful for cleaning up generated HTML, fixing malformed markup, and ensuring consistent formatting.</p>
